metadata.name: Detachment
metadata.description:
Sitting at the coffee shop, staring at my screen  
Numbers and figures, a financial scene  
My mind begins to wander, to a different place  
A feeling of detachment, from the work I face  
I watch the world go by,  
The morning rush is hectic,  
But I'm in my own supply.  
I'm here but not quite present,  
My thoughts drift far away,  
Detached from all the chaos,  
Just here to work and play.  
The scent of roasting beans,  
The clink of porcelain cups,  
All blend into the background,  
As I type, with steady ups.  
I find a sense of comfort,  
In this detachment state,  
The coffee shop's my haven,  
A place to contemplate.  
And as the day wears on,  
My work may take its toll,  
But the coffee shop's my refuge,  
A place to soothe my soul.
